16 "§ 90-753. Scope of practice; limitations.
17 (a) The Board shall establish licensure standards for the following radiologic imaging
18 and radiation therapy modalities:
19 (1) Computed tomography.
20 (2) Cardiac invasive specialist.
21 (3) Cardiac electrophysiology specialist.
22 (4) Diagnostic medical sonography.
23 (5) Limited practice radiographer.
24 (6) Magnetic resonance.
25 (7) Nuclear medicine technologist.
26 (8) Radiation therapist.
27 (9) Radiographer.
28 (10) Radiologist assistant.
29 (b) A person licensed in medical imaging or radiation therapy under this Article may use
30 radioactive substances, equipment emitting ionizing radiation or nonionizing radiation for
31 medical imaging, or radiation therapy procedures only by prescription of an individual authorized
32 by the State to prescribe medical imaging or radiation therapy procedures and under the
33 supervision of a licensed practitioner.
34 (c) Individuals licensed as limited practice radiographers shall perform tasks only within
35 the scope of the specific permit issued to them as provided in G.S. 90-756(c)(1) under the
36 supervision of a licensed practitioner or radiographer and shall not perform computed
37 tomography, diagnostic medical sonography, fluoroscopy, mammography, magnetic resonance
38 imaging, radiation therapy, mobile imaging procedures, or imaging procedures using contrast
39 media.
40 (d) Individuals licensed as cardiovascular invasive specialists shall be registered and
41 licensed to perform, under the supervision of a qualified physician, radiographic procedures
42 using external ionizing radiation to produce fluoroscopic images. To qualify for a license under
43 this subsection, an applicant shall meet all of the following requirements:
44 (1) Possess a high school diploma or equivalent.
45 (2) Possess a current certification in advanced cardiac life support.
46 (3) Complete an accredited cardiovascular technology program.
47 (4) Possess current credentials as a registered cardiovascular invasive specialist
48 offered by Cardiovascular Credentialing International, Cardiac Interventional
49 Radiography, or Cardiovascular Interventional Radiography, as offered by the
50 American Registry Radiologic Technologists or other certification
51 organization as approved by the Board.
