1 (e) Individuals licensed as cardiovascular electrophysiology specialists shall be
2 registered and licensed to perform, under the supervision of a qualified physician, radiographic
3 procedures using external ionizing radiation to produce fluoroscopic images. To qualify for a
4 license under this subsection, an applicant shall meet all of the following requirements:
5 (1) Possess a high school diploma or equivalent.
6 (2) Possess a certificate or degree in health science or possess two years of
7 full-time work experience in diagnostic and interventional cardiac
8 electrophysiology.
9 (3) Graduate from an accredited program in electrophysiology.
10 (4) Possess current credentials as a registered cardiovascular electrophysiology
11 specialist offered by Cardiovascular Credentialing International or other
