13 (f) Effective January 1, 2026, all individuals licensed to perform medical imaging and
14 radiation therapy who perform computed tomography for diagnostic purposes must be certified
15 in computed tomography by the American Registry of Radiologic Technologists, the Nuclear
16 Medicine Technology Certification Board, or another certification organization recognized by
17 the Board.
18 (g) A person licensed to perform nuclear medicine technology may perform computed
19 tomography for attenuation correction and localization on hybrid imaging equipment.
20 (h) A person licensed to perform radiation therapy may perform computed tomography
21 or other modalities for treatment planning purposes.
22 (i) A person licensed to perform radiography may perform fluoroscopy and bone
23 densitometry.
24 (j) A person licensed as a radiologist assistant shall not interpret images, make diagnoses,
25 or prescribe medications or therapies.
26 "§ 90-754. Medical Imaging and Radiation Therapy Board of Examiners.
27 (a) Composition of Board. – The North Carolina Medical Imaging and Radiation Therapy
28 Board of Examiners is hereby created. The Board shall consist of a maximum of nine members
29 appointed by the Governor and shall serve at the pleasure of the Governor. The initial Board shall
30 be appointed within 90 days following the effective date of this section. The members of the
31 Board shall include:
32 (1) One licensed nuclear medicine technologist.
33 (2) One licensed practitioner who is a radiologist and supervises medical imaging
34 or radiation therapy professionals.
35 (3) One certified radiological or therapeutic physicist.
36 (4) One licensed radiation therapist.
37 (5) One licensed computed tomography technologist or radiographer.
38 (6) One licensed magnetic resonance imaging technologist or licensed
39 sonographer.
40 (7) One radiologist assistant.
41 (8) One retired medical imaging professional as public member.
42 (9) One licensed radiography educator.
43 (b) Board Member Qualifications for Appointment. – In addition to the requirements of
44 subsection (a) of this section, Board members shall meet the following qualifications:
45 (1) Each Board member shall be a resident of the State of North Carolina.
46 (2) The public member shall be at least 21 years of age.
47 (3) Except for the public member and the licensed practitioners, each Board
48 member shall have at least two years of experience performing medical
49 imaging or radiation therapy in the modality for which the Board member is
50 appointed.
