1 (c) Terms of Office. – The terms of office shall be three years, except that the terms of
2 the members appointed to the initial Board shall be as follows: three members shall be appointed
3 for a term of one year, three members for a term of two years, and three members for a term of
4 three years. Vacancies shall be filled for an unexpired term only in the manner provided by the
5 original appointment. No member shall be eligible for appointment to serve more than two
6 consecutive terms.
7 (d) Temporary Board Exemption to License Requirements. – A person who performs
8 medical imaging or radiation therapy procedures and is appointed to the initial Board shall not
9 be required to hold a valid license issued by the Board until 12 months after the first issuance of
10 a license by the Board.
11 (e) Compensation and Expenses. – Each member of the Board shall receive per diem and
12 reimbursement for travel and subsistence as provided in G.S. 93B-5.
13 (f) Officers. – The officers of the Board shall be a chair and a vice-chair, and other
14 officers deemed necessary by the Board to carry out the purposes of this Article. All officers shall
15 be elected annually by the Board for one-year terms and shall serve until their successors are
16 elected and qualified.
17 (g) Meetings. – The Board shall hold four meetings each year, once per quarter, to
18 conduct business and to review the standards and rules for improving the administration of
19 medical imaging or radiation therapy procedures. The Board shall establish the procedures for
20 calling, holding, and conducting regular and special meetings. A majority of Board members
21 constitutes a quorum.
22 (h) Meeting Attendance. – A member of the Board who fails to attend three meetings in
23 an 18-month period shall forfeit the member's seat unless the chair, upon written request from
24 the member, finds that the member should be excused from a meeting because of illness or death
25 of a family member.
26 (i) Quorum. – A majority of the voting members of the Board shall constitute a quorum.
27 No action may be taken by the Board except by affirmative vote of the majority of those present
28 and voting.
29 "§ 90-755. Powers of the Board.
30 The Board shall have the following powers and duties:
31 (1) Administer this Article.
32 (2) Issue interpretations of this Article.
33 (3) Adopt rules as may be necessary to carry out the provisions of this Article.
34 (4) Establish the scope of practice for each license or permit type issued by the
35 Board.
36 (5) Employ and fix the compensation of personnel that the Board determines is
37 necessary to carry into effect the provisions of this Article and incur other
38 expenses necessary to effectuate this Article.
39 (6) Examine and determine the qualifications and fitness of applicants for
40 licensure, renewal of licensure, and reciprocal licensure. The Board may, in
41 its discretion, revise the licensing requirements of this Article for areas of
42 North Carolina that the Board deems too remote to contain enough qualified
43 licensees to perform medical imaging or radiation therapy procedures on
44 humans for diagnostic or therapeutic purposes.
45 (7) Set requirements for continuing education as a requirement for license
46 renewal. The Board may review and accept the continuing education and
47 recertification or continuing competency requirements established by a
48 medical imaging or radiation therapy certification organization for license
49 renewal.
50 (8) Issue, renew, deny, suspend, or revoke licenses and carry out any disciplinary
51 actions authorized by this Article.
