17 "§ 90-756. Requirements for licensure.
18 (a) A person seeking to obtain a license for a radiologic imaging or radiation therapy
19 modality shall comply with each of the following requirements:
20 (1) At least 18 years of age at the time of application.
21 (2) Has a high school diploma or has passed an approved equivalency test.
22 (b) Limited Practice Radiographer. – In addition to the requirements of subsection (a) of
23 this section, a person seeking to obtain a license as a limited radiologist assistant shall comply
24 with each of the following requirements:
25 (1) Successfully complete a course of study in limited X-ray machine operation
26 approved by the Board.
27 (2) Pass an examination in limited X-ray machine operation approved by the
28 Board from the following examinations:
29 a. The American Registry of Radiologic Technologists limited X-ray
30 machine operator examination for limited bone density, chest,
31 extremities, spine, skull/sinus, and podiatric radiography.
32 b. The International Society for Clinical Densitometry examination in
33 clinical bone densitometry.
34 c. A certification organization recognized by the Board.
35 (c) Magnetic Resonance Technologist License. – In addition to the requirements of
36 subsection (a) of this section, a person seeking to obtain a license as a magnetic resonance
37 technologist shall comply with each of the following requirements:
38 (1) Successfully complete a course of study in magnetic resonance imaging or a
39 course in radiography and additional educational requirements in magnetic
40 resonance technology approved by the Board.
41 (2) Possess current certification and registration in radiography from the
42 American Registry of Radiologic Technologists or current certification and
43 registration in magnetic resonance from the American Registry of Radiologic
44 Technologists or a certification organization approved by the Board.
45 (3) By January 1, 2026, all applicants for a license under this subsection shall be
46 certified in magnetic resonance under subdivision (2) of this subsection.
47 (d) Nuclear Medicine Technologist License. – In addition to the requirements of
48 subsection (a) of this section, a person seeking to obtain a license as a nuclear medicine
49 technologist shall comply with each of the following requirements:
50 (1) Successfully complete a course of study in nuclear medicine technology
51 approved by the Board.
