11 "§ 90-758. Issuance of license; temporary license; display of license.
12 (a) Issuance of License. – The Board shall issue a license to an applicant who meets the
13 requirements for licensure specified in this Article and the regulations adopted by the Board,
14 verified by oath or affirmation, upon payment of a fee as provided in G.S. 90-761.
15 (b) The Board may issue a license with authorization to perform more than one medical
16 imaging or radiation therapy modality if the person is qualified in each modality.
17 (c) Temporary License. – The Board may issue a temporary license to any person whose
18 license or license renewal may be pending or when issuance is for providing medical imaging or
19 radiation therapy services to medically underserved areas as determined by the Board.
20 (d) New graduates awaiting national certification may be issued a provisional license for
21 employment purposes for a period not to exceed one year.
22 (e) Temporary License for Cross-Training. – A person licensed under this Article may
23 apply to the Board for a temporary license in an additional medical imaging or radiation therapy
24 modality to complete clinical experience requirements for an applicable training pathway
25 established by a certification organization recognized by the Board. Temporary licenses issued
26 for training purposes shall expire three years after issuance.
27 (f) Display of License; License to Be Available Upon Request. – The copy of the current
28 license of all license holders must be maintained at their places of employment.
29 "§ 90-759. Educational programs approved by the Board.
30 (a) In order to obtain approval by the Board, educational programs in medical imaging
31 or radiation therapy shall (i) be offered by a medical facility or educational institution and (ii) be
32 affiliated with one or more hospitals or clinics to provide the requisite clinical education.
33 (b) The curriculum for each course of study in medical imaging or radiation therapy shall
34 be no less stringent than the standards approved by the Joint Review Committee on Education in
35 Radiologic Technology, the Joint Review Committee on Education in Nuclear Medicine
36 Technology, the Commission on Accreditation of Allied Health Education Programs, or other
37 educational accreditation agency approved by the Board.
38 "§ 90-760. License renewal; reciprocity.
39 (a) Every license issued under this Article shall expire on the last day of the licensee's
40 month of birth in the second year following the year of issuance. A licensee who fails to renew a
41 license prior to the expiration date shall submit an application for reinstatement to obtain
42 licensure. The license shall be renewed upon the payment of a renewal fee, as provided in
43 G.S. 90-761, if, at the time of application for renewal, the applicant is not in violation of this
44 Article and has complied with any continuing education requirements pursuant to rules adopted
45 by the Board.
46 (b) The Board shall notify a licensee at least 60 days in advance of the expiration of his
47 or her license. The licensee shall inform the Board of any change of the licensee's address. Each
48 licensee is responsible for renewing his or her license before the expiration date. Licenses that
49 are not renewed automatically lapse.
